  m_Name: EntryText
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::EntryTextList
  entries:
  - Title: ENCYCLOPAEDIA OF WELSH MYTHOS
    Text: "GWYN AP NUDD\r\nIn the ancient traditions of the Cymry, Gwyn ap Nudd is
      feared as the sovereign of Annwn, the shadowy Otherworld. He is a lord of the
      departed, often said to ride through the mist alongside his spectral hounds,
      the C\u0175n Annwn, to gather the souls of the fallen.\r\nThe old bards describe
      him not as a gentle guide, but as a fierce, unyielding warlord. According to
      the ancient texts, his very existence is bound to conflict. He is cursed to
      fight a brutal, never-ending duel against his bitter rival every May Day until
      the end of time\u2026\r\n"
  - Title: A Dynamical Theory of the Electromagnetic Field.
    Text: "By J. Clerk Maxwell.\r\nReceived October 27, - Read December 8, 1864.\r\n-
      Property of Charles Brawlight\u2019s personal library -\r\nPART I - INTRODUCTORY.\r\nThe
      most obvious mechanical phenomenon in electrical and magnetical experiments
      is the mutual action by which bodies in certain states set each other in motion
      while still at a sensible distance from each other\u2026\r\n(This is revolutionary
      work. Perhaps it could finally explain the apparition I saw all those years
      ago that bent electricity around itself. What if apparitions themselves possess
      electromagnetic properties? I shall research this.)"
  - Title: "RESEARCH LOG N\xBA 44 "
    Text: After multiple experiments with visible electromagnetic radiation, light,
      I successfully made contact with a spirit from the dead. Using electric arc
      lamps I communicated with them. I am yet unsure how. I posed questions, instructing
      the spirit to manipulate the lamp's intensity to answer them. He claimed to
      be Iwan, the gardener from my childhood. It answered questions only he could
      possibly know. This shall change everything.
  - Title: "RESEARCH LOG N\xBA 56 "
    Text: "I made contact with something else. It is not the soul of the deceased.
      It claims to be\u2026 more, a ruler of this other land. A world where all the
      deceased roam under its rule. Hell? Annwn? I asked for passage to visit its
      realm. It would further my research even more. I need to see it. It answered
      that I would visit when death knocks at my door. But I must visit now and come
      back to share my findings with mother science. I tried to communicate my resolve,
      but I lost contact with the entity. I need a device more potent than these
      arc lamps. Their light is too dim."
  - Title: "RESEARCH LOG N\xBA 67 "
    Text: 'After testing many materials, I have settled upon calcite crystals. Their
      phosphorescent properties make them ideal amplifiers of light. I theorise that
      light acts as a bridge between the realm of the dead and ours. The spirits
      must be capable of sensing electromagnetic disturbances and interacting with
      them. As such, by illuminating these crystals with my lantern, they shall become
      beacons to the other world. '
  - Title: "RESEARCH LOG N\xBA 69"
    Text: "I established contact with the superior entity once again, thanks to the
      power of the crystals. I asked for safe passage to its realm. To cross the
      threshold and return. It answered that I must first prove my power. To show
      my dominance over others of my kind. It asked for a summoning ritual. I shall
      prepare it.\r\nI will gather more calcite crystals and distribute them throughout
      the halls and corridors of my mansion. I shall light them all, and their light
      combined will be a beacon powerful enough to command the respect of this otherworldly
      ruler. No other of my kind could possibly achieve this. And it shall open the
      door for me. I will step into the realm of the dead and return, advancing humanity\u2019s
      knowledge beyond our wildest dreams."
  - Title: THE NORTH WALES CHRONICLE
    Text: "- November 3rd 1882 -\nSUDDEN DEMISE OF LORD BRAWLIGHT\r\nMysterious Scene
      at Aberglyn Mansion\r\nIn the early hours of yesterday morning, a most grim
      discovery was made at the Brawlight manor. A local tradesman, arriving for
      his customary weekly delivery at six o'clock, discovered the lifeless body
      of Lord Charles Brawlight within the halls of his manor.\r\nThe circumstances
      of the nobleman\u2019s passing are most baffling. Reports indicate that the
      deceased was found contorted in an unnatural fashion, his countenance frozen
      in a look of utter terror, and entirely encircled by an inexplicable arrangement
      of peculiar crystals. The local physician has attributed the death to cardiac
      arrest, estimating that the lord must have expired several days prior. However,
      the lack of prior illness, combined with the bizarre state of the scene, has
      left the authorities mystified."
  - Title: 'To Gwyneth Pritchard '
    Text: "Dear Gwyneth,\r\nHow fares Cardiff, my love? How was the city after the
      Swansea earthquake? What a misfortune that it was so shaken mere days before
      your arrival.\r\nHere, things continue quiet as always. Well, not so quiet.
      A few nights past, Megan\u2019s children snuck out and went to the old manor.
      They came back screaming and weeping. They swear a door slammed shut by itself.
      I confess, I scarcely know what to believe. Perhaps they were merely unnerved
      by all the ghost stories. But, that night wasn\u2019t windy at all!\r\nI wouldn't
      be surprised if, after all the strangeness surrounding Brawlight\u2019s death
      and the curious things he researched, his spirit remained bound to haunt his
      old estate. Mayhaps we can venture a look when you return, dear.\r\nMiss you,\r\nEllis"
  - Title: 'ABERGLYN: COME AND VISIT! '
    Text: 'Nestled beneath the beautiful Clwydian Range, the quaint village of Aberglyn
      offers rolling meadows, quiet woodlands, and a warm Welsh welcome. Perfect
      for a peaceful retreat!

      Stroll along the village high street, admire
      the old stone chapel, cross the tranquil bridge over the river, or climb to
      the clock tower for some fine views.

      Only 15 miles from Wrexham, Aberglyn:
      come and visit!'
  - Title: Peggy Bramble's Diary <3
    Text: "Sunday, October 28th, 1967\r\nDear diary,\r\nI arrived in Aberglyn today!
      I took a stroll around the town while looking for the inn. It really is beautiful.
      I loved the clock tower! But I must not get distracted. I\u2019m here to investigate
      the mysterious death of Lord Charles Brawlight.\r\nI\u2019ve already asked
      a few locals about the late Lord and his estate. Most of them genuinely believe
      the place is haunted. They say he was searching for a way to cross into the
      realm of the dead. It\u2019s fantastic! This is going to make for a brilliant
      write-up, maybe even a front-page scoop. I can feel it!\r\nI\u2019ll head up
      to the old manor to see it for myself tonight. Wish me luck!"
  - Title: Peggy Bramble's Diary <3
    Text: "Monday, October 29th, 1967\r\nDear diary,\r\nWow! So much happened last
      night! I was exploring the grim halls of the manor, examining those strange
      crystals, when a heavy metal door concealed in the wall simply... opened on
      its own. But, despite my fear I managed to venture inside.\r\nI found Lord
      Brawlight\u2019s original journals. The rumors were true! He contacted the
      ruler of the otherworld, who promised him safe passage if he performed a ritual.
      But Charles died. Maybe because he misunderstood the entity\u2019s demand?
      Maybe it isn't just about lighting the crystals? Maybe it wants a competition.
      Two people fighting for control of the crystals\u2026\r\nThis is bigger than
      I ever imagined! I struggle to wrap my head around this all being real, but
      after seeing a massive door moving on its own, I think I\u2019m ready to believe.
      If it all works out I might just be the first journalist in history to report
      directly from the afterlife!"
  - Title: To James Evans
    Text: "Alright James,\r\nYou have to come back to town! I don\u2019t know if
      you\u2019ve been keeping up with the news, but Aberglyn has been buzzing with
      outsiders ever since that journalist from London snooped around the old manor.
      People from all over the country are coming in and competing in the ritual
      at the old Brawlight estate. There\u2019s even a bloke with the head of a moth!
      Apparently, whoever wins gets to visit the afterlife and come back. Talk about
      New Age eh?\r\nWhen are you coming down to have a light-off with me? If you
      win, give your mum my regards!\r\nCheers, Madoc"
